The Scottish actor Sir Sean Connery alias James Bond has passed away at the age of 90, his family has confirmed. He was best known for his portrayal of James Bond, being the first to bring the role to the big screen and appearing in seven of the spy thrillers. According to BBC, Sir Sean died peacefully in his sleep, while in the Bahamas, having been "unwell for some time", his son said. His acting career spanned five decades and he won an Oscar in 1988 for his role in “The Untouchables.” Other famous Sir Sean's films are The Hunt for Red October, Highlander, Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade and The Rock. 